  <title>OCCI Platform</title>

  <para>The OCCI Platform specification defines kinds and extensions relating
  to management of cloud platform services (PaaS).</para>

  <table>
    <title>Common Attributes</title>

    <tgroup cols="3">
      <colspec align="center" />

      <thead>
        <row>
          <entry align="left">Attribute</entry>

          <entry>Type</entry>

          <entry>Description</entry>
        </row>
      </thead>

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry
          align="left"><computeroutput>occi.platform.version</computeroutput></entry>

          <entry>Float (e.g. 1.0)</entry>

          <entry>Version of the OCCI Platform specification</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </table>

  <section>
    <title>Kinds</title>

    <para>Cloud platform services can be modeled using the following primary
    kinds:</para>

    <table>
      <title>Kinds</title>

      <tgroup cols="3">
        <colspec align="center" />

        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry align="left">Kind</entry>

            <entry>URI</entry>

            <entry>Description</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry align="left"><computeroutput>queue</computeroutput></entry>

            <entry><uri>http://purl.org/occi/kind/queue</uri></entry>

            <entry>An ordered list of tasks or messages</entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry
            align="left"><computeroutput>database</computeroutput></entry>

            <entry><uri>http://purl.org/occi/kind/database</uri></entry>

            <entry>An organised body of related information</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>

    <section>
      <title>Queue</title>

      <para>A queue manages an ordered list of tasks or messages for
      transmission and/or processing.</para>

      <table>
        <title>Queue Attributes</title>

        <tgroup cols="3">
          <colspec align="center" />

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry align="left">Attribute</entry>

              <entry>Type</entry>

              <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry
              align="left"><computeroutput>occi.queue.policy</computeroutput></entry>

              <entry>Enum (fifo, filo)</entry>

              <entry>Status of the compute resource</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Database</title>

      <para>A database manages an organised body of related
      information.</para>

      <table>
        <title>Database Attributes</title>

        <tgroup cols="3">
          <colspec align="center" />

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry align="left">Attribute</entry>

              <entry>Type</entry>

              <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry
              align="left"><computeroutput>occi.database.size</computeroutput></entry>

              <entry>Float (10^9 bytes)</entry>

              <entry>Database size in gigabytes (e.g.
              <computeroutput>10</computeroutput>,
              <computeroutput>0.5</computeroutput>)</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Extensions</title>

    <para>Various extensions provide for more advanced management
    functionality such as billing, monitoring and reporting.</para>
  </section>

